{"title_page": "Shirley LeFlore", "text_new": "'''Shirley LeFlore''' is one of [[St. Louis, Missouri|St. Louis]]' most influential performance art [[poets]].<ref>[http://news-info.wustl.edu/news/page/normal/6491.html Music and Musicians of the Black Artists' Group in St. Louis<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>  Before she became a board member for Word In Motion, she split her time between performances in New York City and teaching creative writing at the [[University of Missouri\u2013St. Louis]]. One of the premiere women's voices in St. Louis, Shirley has been a part of many underground activists poetry organizations including the [[Black Artists' Group]] and Harmony. A book of her poetry is scheduled for release, and she has received the Warrior Poet Award.{{Citation needed|date=March 2008}}\n<!-- ''Michael O'Brian'' -->\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080518105158/http://www.stlouispoetrycenter.org/readings/   LeFlore's Readings]\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Leflore, Shirley}}\n[[Category:Writers from St. Louis]]\n[[Category:University of Missouri\u2013St. Louis people]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:African-American poets]]\n\n\n{{US-poet-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Shirley LeFlore''' is one of [[St. Louis, Missouri|St. Louis]]' most influential performance art [[poets]].<ref>[http://news-info.wustl.edu/news/page/normal/6491.html Music and Musicians of the Black Artists' Group in St. Louis<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>  Before she became a board member for Word In Motion, she split her time between performances in New York City and teaching creative writing at the [[University of Missouri\u2013St. Louis]]. One of the premiere women's voices in St. Louis, Shirley has been a part of many underground activists poetry organizations including the [[Black Artists' Group]] and Harmony. A book of her poetry is scheduled for release, and she has received the Warrior Poet Award.{{Citation needed|date=March 2008}}\n<!-- ''Michael O'Brian'' -->\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080518105158/http://www.stlouispoetrycenter.org/readings/   LeFlore's Readings]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Leflore, Shirley}}\n[[Category:Writers from St. Louis]]\n[[Category:University of Missouri\u2013St. Louis people]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:African-American poets]]\n\n\n{{US-poet-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shirley_LeFlore"}
